DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260601
SUMMARY:Deadline: Stroom Den Haag: PRO Grants 2026 (Research / Projects / P
 rogrammes / Investment)
DESCRIPTION:Stroom Den Haag's PRO grants support professional visual artist
 s registered with Stroom in The Hague through four schemes: PRO Research (
 research and development for new work)\, PRO Projects (project realisation
 )\, PRO Programmes (multi-stage artistic programmes spanning research\, pr
 oduction and presentation)\, and PRO Investment (investment in artistic pr
 actice\, e.g. equipment\, studio\, professional development). Three remain
 ing 2026 application rounds: 31 May\, 6 September and 25 October 2026. ELI
 GIBILITY: professional visual artists registered with Stroom in the munici
 pality of The Hague (tightly geographic). Amounts vary by scheme and propo
 sal\, typically EUR 2\,500 to EUR 20\,000+.\n\nOrganisation: Stroom Den Ha
 ag\nLocation: The Hague\, Netherlands (eligibility restricted to professio
 nal visual artists registered with Stroom in the municipality of The Hague
 )\nAward: Four schemes - PRO Research\, PRO Projects\, PRO Programmes\, an
 d PRO Investment - with amounts typically EUR 2\,500 to EUR 20\,000+ depen
 ding on scheme and proposal.\nDuration: Project-based\n\nMore: https://www
 .stroom.nl/en/stroom-for-artists/financial-support/pro-research
