 unrestricted financial support\, exposure and recognition to contemporary 
 visual artists. Three Awardees receive $15\,000 each (use freely)\; Finali
 sts not chosen as Awardees receive an honorarium. Awardees join the Artadi
 a Network and get a dedicated webpage on the Artadia Online Artist Registr
 y. PROCESS: open call (May 1 - June 1\, 2026)\; first-round jury of three 
 curators (one local) selects six Finalists\; second-round jury conducts 45
 -minute virtual studio visits\; three Awardees announced. ELIGIBILITY: con
 temporary visual artist making work for a contemporary-art context\; livin
 g and working in the Bay Area's eligible counties and resident there for 2
 + consecutive years prior to the deadline\; not currently enrolled (or pla
 nning to enrol) in an art-related degree programme\; have never received a
 n Artadia/Art Council award of $10\,000 or more (former finalists may re-a
 pply). Apply via Submittable only.\n\nOrganisation: Artadia\nLocation: San
  Francisco Bay Area\, California\, United States\nAward: Three Awardees ea
 ch receive a US$15\,000 unrestricted award. Finalists not chosen as Awarde
 es receive an honorarium. Awardees also access the Artadia Network and the
  Online Artist Registry. No application fee.\nDuration: One-off award\; tw
 o-round jury (application review + virtual studio visits)\n\nMore: https:/
 /artadia.org/awards
URL:https://artadia.org/awards
LOCATION:San Francisco Bay Area\, California\, United States
