UID:naomi-anolic-early-career-jewish-visual-arts-award-2026@artificialnouve
 au.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260608T110715Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260601
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260602
SUMMARY:Deadline: Naomi Anolic Early Career Jewish Visual Arts Award 2026
DESCRIPTION:Annual award providing momentum for early-career Jewish visual 
 artists for a specific project. The 2026 cycle focuses on the fine arts: p
 ainting\, drawing\, sculpture and mixed media. Recipients must provide a b
 rief artist statement and visual documentation of the supported work at ye
 ar end\, and must credit the Naomi Anolic Early Career Jewish Visual Arts 
 Award in any exhibition or publication of the supported work. ELIGIBILITY:
  active early-career Jewish artists aged 25 to 35\; students may not apply
 . APPLY with a max 600-word proposal (why you're applying\, why you're ear
 ly-career\, project/focus\, how the award will help\, how Judaism informs 
 and is realised in your work - overt Jewish imagery is not required)\, 10 
 jpg images (max 1024px longest side\, max 4 MB each)\, an image list\, an 
 up-to-2-page CV/resume\, and an artist website (or social-media link if no
  site). Award announcement by September 2026. Questions: info@anolicfamily
 award.org.\n\nOrganisation: Anolic Family Award\nLocation: Online applicat
 ion (open to early-career Jewish artists)\nAward: $1\,000 award for one ea
 rly-career Jewish artist. No application fee.\nDuration: One-off award\; p
 roject supported within the award year\, with a final artist statement and
  visual documentation due at year end\n\nMore: https://anolicfamilyaward.o
 rg/naomi-anolic-award
URL:https://anolicfamilyaward.org/naomi-anolic-award
LOCATION:Online application (open to early-career Jewish artists)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:gasworks-residency-artists-based-in-greece-2026@artificialnouveau.githu
 b.io
DTSTAMP:20260608T110715Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260601
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260602
SUMMARY:Deadline: Gasworks Residency 2026: Artists Based in Greece
DESCRIPTION:Gasworks residency open call for a contemporary visual artist a
 t a pivotal point in their career\, based in Greece. The 11-week\, fully f
 unded residency takes place at Gasworks in London 30 September - 15 Decemb
 er 2026. The programme supports professional development\, cultural exchan
 ge and artistic experimentation\; up to 20 residencies per year\, self-led
 \, non-prescriptive and process-based. Selection panel includes Gasworks r
 eps + external advisors with specialist knowledge of the Greek and UK cont
 emporary art scenes\; a shortlist of four artists is invited to a short on
 line interview before the final decision. ELIGIBILITY: contemporary visual
  artists (not duos/collectives) based in Greece\, with at least a moderate
  level of spoken English\; artists studying outside Greece may apply if th
 ey have a permanent address in Greece and will be living there during the 
 residency dates. Priority is given to artists who have not previously work
 ed or studied in London. APPLY: one PDF (max 15MB) with cover sheet\, 250-
 word practice statement\, 250-word residency-plan statement\, up to 15 ima
 ges or video/sound clips of recent work (with captions)\, CV (max 3 pages)
 \, and any relevant documentation\; spoken responses can substitute the wr
 itten statements via embedded video/audio links. Deadline 1 June 2026\, 1p
 m UK time. Supported by Thalia and Alex Haidas.\n\nOrganisation: Gasworks 
 (London)\nLocation: Gasworks\, London\, United Kingdom\nAward: Fully funde
 d 11-week residency: 24/7 private studio at Gasworks\, single-room accommo
 dation in Gasworks Residency House\, economy return flights + taxi transfe
 rs from home country\, all visa costs and visa-application support\, weekl
 y stipend of GBP 175 for living expenses\, materials budget up to GBP 800\
 , prepaid TFL Zones 1+2 travel card for the residency\, studio visits with
  staff/curators/artists\, an Open Studio event and presentation\, dedicate
 d residency page on the Gasworks website with a short video interview\, ne
 tworking and at least two individual studio visits\, plus admin/pastoral/c
 uratorial support. No application fee.\nDuration: 11 weeks: 30 September -
  15 December 2026\n\nMore: https://www.gasworks.org.uk/opportunities/resid
 ency-open-call-for-artists-based-in-greece-2026
URL:https://www.gasworks.org.uk/opportunities/residency-open-call-for-artis
 ts-based-in-greece-2026
LOCATION:Gasworks\, London\, United Kingdom
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
