SUMMARY:Deadline: Gasworks Residency 2026: Artists Based in Aotearoa New Ze
 aland
DESCRIPTION:Gasworks residency open call for an early-career contemporary v
 isual artist based in Aotearoa New Zealand. The 11-week\, fully funded res
 idency takes place at Gasworks in London 30 September - 15 December 2026. 
 Self-led\, non-prescriptive\, process-based programme supporting professio
 nal development\, cultural exchange and experimentation. Selection by pane
 l of Gasworks staff and external advisors with specialist knowledge of the
  Aotearoa NZ and UK contemporary-art scenes\; priority for artists who hav
 e not yet worked in London\; shortlist of four invited to a short online i
 nterview (week beginning 22 June 2026)\; successful applicant notified the
  week beginning 6 July 2026. ELIGIBILITY: early-career contemporary visual
  artists based in Aotearoa NZ only\; at least moderate spoken English\; no
  duos/collectives\, no accompanying partners/children supported. APPLY: on
 e PDF (max 15MB) with cover sheet\, 250-word practice statement\, 250-word
  residency-plan statement\, up to 15 images/video/sound clips of recent wo
 rk (captions\, up to 100 words per work)\, CV (max 3 pages)\, and any rele
 vant documentation\; spoken responses via embedded video/audio links accep
 ted. Deadline 1 June 2026\, 1pm UK time. Supported by the Jan Warburton Ch
 aritable Trust and Aotearoa NZ Friends of Gasworks\, with additional suppo
 rt from the British Council Aotearoa NZ and the Pacific\, in partnership w
 ith the Office for Contemporary Art Aotearoa.\n\nOrganisation: Gasworks (L
 ondon)\, with the Office for Contemporary Art Aotearoa\nLocation: Gasworks
 \, London\, United Kingdom\nAward: Fully funded 11-week residency: 24/7 pr
 ivate studio at Gasworks\, single-room accommodation in Gasworks Residency
  House\, economy return flights + taxi transfers from home country (1 cabi
 n + 1 hold bag)\, all visa costs and visa-application support\, weekly sti
 pend of GBP 175\, materials budget up to GBP 800\, prepaid TFL Zones 1+2 t
 ravel card\, studio visits\, an Open Studio event on Saturday 5 December 2
 026\, a dedicated residency page on the Gasworks website with short video 
 interview\, networking + at least two individual studio visits\, plus admi
 n/pastoral/curatorial support. No application fee.\nDuration: 11 weeks: 30
  September - 15 December 2026\n\nMore: https://www.gasworks.org.uk/opportu
 nities/residency-open-call-for-artists-based-in-aotearoa-new-zealand-2026
URL:https://www.gasworks.org.uk/opportunities/residency-open-call-for-artis
 ts-based-in-aotearoa-new-zealand-2026
LOCATION:Gasworks\, London\, United Kingdom
END:VEVENT
