UID:craftopia-material-dialogues-textile-waste-residency-2026@artificialnou
 veau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260608T110715Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260615
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260616
SUMMARY:Deadline: CrafTopia Creative Hub: Material Dialogues Textile Waste 
 Residency 2026 (Thessaloniki\, Greece)
DESCRIPTION:CrafTopia Creative Hub\, a Thessaloniki-based cultural and crea
 tive hub supporting artistic expression\, learning and community engagemen
 t through residencies\, workshops\, exhibitions and collaborative projects
 \, opens a Material Dialogues textile-waste residency for five visual arti
 sts. THEME: sustainability\; the residency invites artists to work with te
 xtile waste sourced from industries operating in the same historic buildin
 g as CrafTopia\, emphasising the creative process over the final product. 
 Participants are encouraged to experiment and collaborate\, using their ar
 tistic skills in innovative ways with mixed media including paper and text
 ile. ELIGIBILITY: visual artists who reside in eligible Culture Moves Euro
 pe countries\; residency funded by the European Union and the Goethe-Insti
 tut under Culture Moves Europe. SUPPORT: accommodation\, shared working sp
 ace\, mentoring\, networking opportunities\, travel reimbursement\, access
  to materials\, administrative/logistical support\, and a daily allowance.
  RESIDENCY DATES: 15 October - 13 November 2026 (30 days). DEADLINE: 15 Ju
 ne 2026. APPLY via the CrafTopia open-call page.\n\nOrganisation: CrafTopi
 a Creative Hub (under Culture Moves Europe\, funded by the European Union 
 and the Goethe-Institut)\nLocation: Thessaloniki\, Greece\nAward: Accommod
 ation\; shared working space\; mentoring\; networking opportunities\; trav
 el reimbursement\; access to materials\; administrative and logistical sup
 port\; daily allowance (Culture Moves Europe standard). No application fee
 .\nDuration: 30-day residency from 15 October to 13 November 2026\n\nMore:
  https://craftopia.gr/2026/05/18/open-call-material-dialogues-paper-textil
 es-and-contemporary-craft/
URL:https://craftopia.gr/2026/05/18/open-call-material-dialogues-paper-text
 iles-and-contemporary-craft/
LOCATION:Thessaloniki\, Greece
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:khoj-residency-mental-health-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260608T110715Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260607
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260608
SUMMARY:Deadline: Khoj: Residency on Mental Health 2026 (New Delhi\, India)
DESCRIPTION:Khoj Studios invites Indian and international artists whose pra
 ctice engages with mental health and distress\, critically examining how p
 ain (physical\, psychological\, or historical) shapes both the self and so
 ciety. On-site residency at Khoj Studios in New Delhi\, 3 August - 16 Sept
 ember 2026. THEMATIC FRAME: how is suffering unequally distributed across 
 race\, caste\, class\, gender\, and geography? How do individuals and comm
 unities navigate\, resist\, or reclaim forms of vitality in the face of wa
 r\, colonial legacies\, and systemic inequalities? Rather than defining me
 ntal health and illness solely in medical terms\, the residency is open to
  a range of knowledge systems\, forms of practice\, and diverse concepts o
 f vitality and distress. ENGAGES: clinical and everyday experiences\; myth
  and ritual as alternative or mainstream ways to process pain\; ancestors\
 , spirits\, oral histories\, and expressive traditions as tools of healing
 \; digital cultures\, new technologies\, and clinical subjectivities resha
 ping the self\, anxiety\, coping\, memory and aspiration. Brings together 
 artists and scholars from India and the UK to explore varied forms of vita
 lity and distress shaping contemporary life-worlds. ELIGIBILITY: Indian an
 d international artists working in any medium. SUPPORT: travel to/from Del
 hi\, per-diem\, production budget\; one UK artist additionally supported b
 y OAS's Center for Anthropology and Mental Health Research in Action. DEAD
 LINE: 7 June 2026. APPLY via the Khoj International Residency page.\n\nOrg
 anisation: Khoj Studios (in collaboration with OAS Center for Anthropology
  and Mental Health Research in Action)\nLocation: Khoj Studios\, New Delhi
 \, India\nAward: Travel to and from Delhi\; a per-diem\; and a production 
 budget. One UK artist additionally supported by OAS's Center for Anthropol
 ogy and Mental Health Research in Action. No application fee.\nDuration: O
 n-site residency from 3 August to 16 September 2026\n\nMore: https://khojs
 tudios.org/programme/khoj-international-residency/edition-august-september
 -2026/
URL:https://khojstudios.org/programme/khoj-international-residency/edition-
 august-september-2026/
LOCATION:Khoj Studios\, New Delhi\, India
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:aerowaves-twenty27@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260608T110715Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260715
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260716
SUMMARY:Deadline: Aerowaves Twenty27: Call for Emerging European Choreograp
 hers
DESCRIPTION:Aerowaves selects 20 emerging choreographers based in geographi
 cal Europe each year (the Twenty27 cohort) to have their work presented at
  the Spring Forward festival (14-17 April 2027 in Limerick\, Ireland) and 
 at many of Aerowaves' partners around Europe\; Aerowaves promotes the sele
 cted artists for a year\, creating performance opportunities with partners
 . EVERY APPLICANT (selected or not) has the chance to be programmed by Aer
 owaves network partners\; around 100 performance opportunities per year ar
 e supported by Aerowaves. ELIGIBILITY: applicants must be resident in geog
 raphical Europe\; due to the Russian invasion of Ukraine\, Aerowaves partn
 ers do NOT accept applications of works made in Russia or Belarus. ONE wor
 k per applicant per year. The work must have been produced in geographical
  Europe\; must be 15-40 minutes\; must be finished and have been presented
  to the public (a studio sharing counts\; work-in-progress or rehearsal fo
 otage does NOT). The work should be easily included in a double or triple 
 bill with simple technical requirements\; works created for public/non-con
 ventional spaces and outdoors are welcome. WHAT SELECTED ARTISTS GET: pres
 entation fee at Spring Forward plus travel (within Europe)\, hotel and per
  diem/hospitality for each team member\; a year of Aerowaves website promo
 tion. DEADLINE: 15 July 2026. APPLY via the Aerowaves how-to-apply page.\n
 \nOrganisation: Aerowaves (Spring Forward festival hosted in Limerick\, Ir
 eland)\nLocation: Festival in Limerick\, Ireland (14-17 April 2027) plus p
 artner venues across Europe\; applicants must be resident in geographical 
 Europe\nAward: For presentation at Spring Forward: a fee plus expenses inc
 luding travel within Europe\, hotel and a per diem/hospitality for each te
 am member. Around 100 partner performance opportunities are guaranteed eac
 h year and supported by Aerowaves. Selected applicants additionally receiv
 e a year of Aerowaves promotion (artist profile\, images\, video\, press c
 overage). No application fee.\nDuration: One year of Aerowaves promotion a
 nd partner-network presentations\; presentation at Spring Forward 14-17 Ap
 ril 2027\n\nMore: https://aerowaves.org/artists/how-to-apply/
URL:https://aerowaves.org/artists/how-to-apply/
LOCATION:Festival in Limerick\, Ireland (14-17 April 2027) plus partner ven
 ues across Europe\; applicants must be resident in geographical Europe
END:VEVENT
